<title>USA: GM eyes Delphi unit public offering - WSJ.</title>
<headline>GM eyes Delphi unit public offering - WSJ.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-01-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>As General Motors Corp gets ready to sell the defence business of Hughes Electronics, it is exploring a public offering of a stake in its Delphi Automotive Systems unit, the world's largest automotive parts supplier, The Wall Street Journal reported Friday.</p>
<p>The Journal quotes GM Vice Chairman Harry Pearce as saying the move is one of a number GM is thinking about for Delphi.</p>
<p>Pearce's statement is significant because is shows GM may be willing to give Delphi more autonomy, the newspaper said.</p>
